Question: What do you like/dislike about public transportation.
Answer:

Public transportation is generally cheap than renting or owning a car. In many big citties, like washington DC and Tokyo, public transportation is much cheaper but equally convenient than own a car. Public transportation is also environmental-friendly. subways and a lot of buses use green energy, like electricity and solar power. this keeps the sustainability of the earth.

however, sometimes public transoortation is horrible during rush hours. it is absolutely convenient to take subway in Tokyo whiletravel around, but the subway always overloads during the periods when people commute. 